track.name: Dolphin Dance
comments: This is a badddd man on the keys!
Correction nailed--see Herold55 below: Herbie Hancock (piano) Freddie Hubbard (tp) George Coleman (ts) Ron Carter (b) Tony Williams (dr) 17.3.1965 (van Gelder) Blue Note 4195 (LP "Maiden Voyage")
Could somebody please tell me what album THIS version is from!

Herbie Hancock (piano)    Freddie Hubbard (tp)     George Coleman (ts)
Ron Carter (b)     Tony Williams (dr)
17.3.1965  (van Gelder)  Blue Note 4195  (LP "Maiden Voyage")
Love this tune! But unfortunately, someone messed up the track title. This is actually "Maiden Voyage," not "Dolphin Dance."
One of the great jazz standards.

1972 in the USAF, took a hit of orange acid and listened to this tune all night. Man the sounds I heard! 2009, thirty-seven years older, not acid and I still hear extraordinary, beautiful sounds from this tune. God Bless you Mr. Hancock!

Q -Does it get better than this ...
A -  No.
im still trying to grasp how its possible to write such clever and complex modal changes yet such a perfect melody
Hmm. Someone has scrobbled the track "Maiden Voyage" as "Dolphin Dance". :-(
